column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
The lake is covered with yellow green pine tree dust making readings difficult. This seems to be the heaviest coveringt at this time of year that I can recall.

column1: Lots of weed growth in the last week- warmer weather

column2: clear and calm.....perfect conditions to measure.
Partly cloudy with a slight ripple on the surface of the water. Thermocline estimated at 20 feet using a clinefinder.
Perfect day after many days of wind and several days of very cold weather. Surface temperature 68.2?F- down 10? in one week.
Very clear- 50% clouds- I took two readings to verify the clear condition
Took temp with Cline-finder........thermocline at 26 ft.
Slight chop caused some drift.....too deep to anchor.
Nice conditions. 2 inches of rain 48 hours prior.
